				\begin{document}$$\Delta W=A\cdot exp\left(\frac{{-\Delta t}^{2}}{{2\tau }^{2}}\right)+{W}_{0}$$\end{document}where A is a scaling factor and τ is the time constant. The fitting process revealed a τ = 459 ms, which is on the same order of magnitude as the timescale of synaptic weight modification in biological synapses [85, 86], and similar to another report [87].
